Write the command to list all of the files in your directory, including the hidden files
Suppose you are currently in your home directory.
Write the commands necessary to go into your Documents, add a new file called hello.txt, and write “Hello there!” inside of it.
Write the command necessary to find out what directory you are currently in.
Suppose you are currently in a directory that contains two files called notes.txt and review.txt.
Write the command in order to make a copy of notes.txt and name it notes2.txt. Then, write the command to view review.txt and then delete it.
Suppose you’re in a directory that contains a file named queenLyrics.txt. Write the command necessary to search the file for “is this just fantasy”.
Write the command necessary to create a new user with your name and then switch to it.
